Re: What happens when you die?
by T3rminus on Fri Oct 08, 2010 11:02 pm	([msg=47275]see Re: What happens when you die?[/msg])
You may find it interesting that the Bible does not say that all good people go to heaven. If you read Ecclesiastes chapter nine and verses five and six it says : "For the living are conscious that they will die; but as for the dead, they are conscious of nothing at all, neither do they anymore have wages, because the remembrance of them has been forgotten. 6 Also, their love and their hate and their jealousy have already perished, and they have no portion anymore to time indefinite in anything that has to be done under the sun."It is also mentioned in Psalms chapter 37 and verses 10 and 11: "And just a little while longer, and the wicked one will be no more; And you will certainly give attention to his place, and he will not be. 11 But the meek ones themselves will possess the earth, And they will indeed find their exquisite delight in the abundance of peace." This idea was reflected by Jesus himself when he said in Matthew chapter 5 and verse 5:“Happy are the mild-tempered ones, since they will inherit the earth."As so according to the Bible itself the idea that all good people go to heaven is incorrect as well.I just thought that I would say something also .-Phill
